17:33.783 --> 17:35.970
we definitely did not try.

17:37.538 --> 17:39.290
That's wonderful, Caroline.

17:39.892 --> 17:41.356
<i>Honey, I've got another call.</i>

17:41.481 --> 17:43.520
I'll talk to you later.
Big kiss.

17:50.339 --> 17:51.486
I'm doomed.

17:52.050 --> 17:54.490
My novel's due in a month
and I only have one sentence.

17:54.615 --> 17:56.365
And I don't even like it.

17:57.761 --> 17:59.953
Even that building
is laughing at me.

18:01.593 --> 18:05.090
Do you think the architect purposely
made it look like a gigantic cock?

18:06.941 --> 18:08.241
To humiliate me.

18:21.139 --> 18:23.739
Sorry I couldn't get here sooner.
I was out all day helping Ray.

18:23.864 --> 18:25.979
Come here, come here.
Sit down.

18:26.452 --> 18:28.144
Read this.
Tell me what you think.

18:28.269 --> 18:30.284
It's this week's editorial.

18:30.409 --> 18:31.818
I've got to email that in.

18:31.986 --> 18:34.886
The deadline was half
an hour ago, so hurry up.

18:35.026 --> 18:36.573
This is too much.
You'll be sued.

18:38.409 --> 18:41.532
"Richard Antrem has the brainpower
of someone with tertiary syphilis,

18:41.657 --> 18:44.910
"the penis of a hermaphrodite and the
moral judgment of a subnormal pinhead. "

18:45.124 --> 18:47.959
- You can't publish it as an editorial.
- Why not? It's all true.

18:48.161 --> 18:49.861
But it's libel, slander.

18:50.876 --> 18:52.088
And it's really long.

18:53.098 --> 18:55.675
Did you write this all of today?
I haven't written this much in months.

18:55.843 --> 18:57.469
It's easy when you're inspired.

18:59.360 --> 19:00.510
Keep reading.

19:04.472 --> 19:05.935
Okay, you can't do this.

19:06.366 --> 19:09.493
You say that he has a mouth
like the anus of a starfish

19:09.618 --> 19:12.442
and that he's been suspected
of plagiarism his whole career.

19:12.610 --> 19:14.944
Yeah, so let him try
to prove any of it's untrue.

19:19.347 --> 19:20.784
You remember when you told me

19:20.952 --> 19:23.632
that I needed to be sane
when you were insane?

19:23.757 --> 19:25.663
I don't remember.
What's the matter with you?

19:25.831 --> 19:27.078
It'll be a great issue...

19:27.203 --> 19:29.888
My editorial and the comic
that you did with Ray.

19:31.278 --> 19:33.155
I know Antrem torments you,

19:33.516 --> 19:36.800
but you attack <i>GQ</i>
calling it a women's magazine.

19:36.968 --> 19:39.338
I've had it, really. Seriously,
I can't take it anymore.

19:39.463 --> 19:43.431
They're like a classic playground bully
and you know how you deal with bullies?

19:43.709 --> 19:45.194
- Tell the teacher?
- No no.

19:45.319 --> 19:47.727
You fight back.
You kick 'em in the balls.

19:49.563 --> 19:51.620
Publishing this
is something he would do.

19:53.096 --> 19:54.096
It's not.

19:54.859 --> 19:56.669
It wouldn't be as well written.

19:56.794 --> 19:57.794
And send.

20:09.055 --> 20:11.255
Maybe it's best that I'm sterile.

20:11.726 --> 20:12.809
Don't say that.

20:12.934 --> 20:14.811
I'd make a lousy father anyway.

20:14.936 --> 20:17.187
I couldn't tell a child
all the lies you need to feed them.

20:17.312 --> 20:20.194
- Like what?
- Like 18 years of school is fun.

20:20.319 --> 20:22.068
And that crushing your spirit

20:22.193 --> 20:24.721
to fit in with the rest of the world
is a good thing.

20:25.060 --> 20:27.651
I don't know.
I'd like to have a kid someday.

20:28.176 --> 20:30.015
Except I'd be worry
about that soft spot

20:30.140 --> 20:31.558
on top of their head.

20:31.683 --> 20:33.898
I'd want them to wear
a bicycle helmet all the time.

20:34.066 --> 20:36.188
Wait, soft spot?
What's a soft spot?

20:36.313 --> 20:38.525
The soft spot is like...
It's a very dangerous part

20:38.650 --> 20:39.966
on top of a baby's head.

20:40.091 --> 20:42.456
If you touch on it
it can go right to the brain.

20:44.844 --> 20:46.411
I'll do all the talking.

20:56.044 --> 20:57.380
- Yes?
- Renee Dalton?

20:57.669 --> 20:58.668
Who's asking?

20:58.883 --> 21:00.842
My name is Jonathan Ames.
I'm a private detective.

21:01.049 --> 21:02.861
I'm sorry, what do you want?

21:02.986 --> 21:04.797
My associate and I
have reason to believe

21:04.922 --> 21:07.390
that you may have been
sold illegally obtained sperm.

21:07.911 --> 21:09.350
We'd like to know two things:

21:09.717 --> 21:11.745
do you know are the people
who sold the sperm,

21:11.870 --> 21:13.420
and are you pregnant?

21:14.407 --> 21:16.683
- How did you get my name?
- From the apartment of two women

21:16.808 --> 21:18.818
known to us as Lisa and Michelle...

21:19.323 --> 21:22.364
Real names Margaret Duckett
and Ellen Willis.

21:22.505 --> 21:25.883
My associate actually is the man
whose sperm was stolen by these two.

21:26.008 --> 21:27.702
What's going on?
Who are you?

21:27.951 --> 21:29.913
I'm Jonathan Ames.
I'm a private detective.

21:30.264 --> 21:32.053
Show me some identification.

21:32.950 --> 21:34.751
I'm not officially
a private detective,

21:34.876 --> 21:37.146
but I do have a New Jersey
driver's license.

21:37.421 --> 21:40.351
- Let's go in the house.
- They're here about the sperm we used.

21:40.585 --> 21:41.935
It came from him.

21:43.597 --> 21:45.215
They know Lisa and Michelle.

21:46.560 --> 21:48.181
I'm pregnant with this guy's baby?

21:48.349 --> 21:49.849
- You're pregnant?
- It's early.

21:50.017 --> 21:52.808
- We're not really telling anyone yet.
- That's so exciting.

21:54.527 --> 21:57.232
- That's great that you're pregnant.
- This is bullshit.

21:57.357 --> 21:59.774
We're very happy.
This is what we wanted.

22:00.955 --> 22:02.040
What do you do?

22:02.165 --> 22:04.489
The donor was supposed
to be PhD from Stanford.

22:04.989 --> 22:06.799
I went to the university of Albany.

22:06.924 --> 22:09.004
I studied art.
I'm a cartoonist.

22:09.585 --> 22:11.162
Are you at least a vegan?

22:11.740 --> 22:14.207
We were told the donor would have
very little mercury in his sperm.

22:14.399 --> 22:16.876
Well, I eat fish.
And I eat a lot of meat...

22:18.295 --> 22:20.626
A lot of meat.
But I've had two colonics.

22:21.090 --> 22:24.128
Oh my God, you were supposed to
be a vegan with an average build.

22:24.491 --> 22:25.946
I do have an average build.

22:26.071 --> 22:29.013
I don't believe this. I feel like
Mia Farrow in <i>Rosemary's baby</i>.

22:29.199 --> 22:31.449
Oh, sweetheart, it's not that bad.

22:31.974 --> 22:33.476
Okay, you two get off my porch

22:34.020 --> 22:36.768
- or I'll call 911.
- Don't call 911. I hate 911.

22:37.175 --> 22:38.443
You should be happy.

22:38.568 --> 22:40.521
Ray is a great guy.
He's a wonderful friend.

22:40.646 --> 22:42.399
And I'm sure he has
incredible D.N.A.

22:42.778 --> 22:45.738
I do have good D.N.A. There's
Crohn's disease on my mom's side, but...

22:45.906 --> 22:47.780
Don't ever contact us again.

22:47.905 --> 22:50.705
You're to have nothing
to do with this child.

22:51.458 --> 22:52.458
Come on.

22:52.583 --> 22:53.565
I'm so sorry.

22:54.101 --> 22:55.349
Find me on facebook.

22:59.418 --> 23:00.818
I'm having a baby.

23:01.531 --> 23:03.256
The mother of my child hates me.

23:03.686 --> 23:05.139
It's kind of one of those...

23:08.404 --> 23:09.358
Papa.

23:11.942 --> 23:13.292
Get off my porch.

23:21.642 --> 23:23.250
To your first collaboration.

23:23.375 --> 23:25.125
And to not being sterile.

23:25.560 --> 23:27.565
To having a child
with a woman who hates me.

23:27.690 --> 23:30.240
Here's to being
just like my own father.

23:30.694 --> 23:33.077
Nice editorial, George.
I can't stand Antrem.

23:33.448 --> 23:35.663
I loved that line
about the starfish anus.

23:35.871 --> 23:37.540
